$interpreted: Jihasaha: Sounds like we're close!
Tindoiimu: Okay, this time we'll catch 'em!
Tindoiimu: ...You?
Juan Yun: Uh oh, I've been found out!
Tindoiimu: ...What are you doing here?
Juan Yun: As you can see, I'm setting off fireworks.
Jihasaha: Why would the qilin lord need to sneak around like this, playing with children's toys?
Juan Yun: Well, it is exactly because people are always telling me they're children's toys, and I ought to act more like a lord...
Juan Yun: ...that I have no choice but to be sneaky.
Tindoiimu: ...They're so beautiful... so different from ordinary fireworks...
Juan Yun: The craftsman who made these is the best in the east. Well, "was" the best in the east. He actually stopped making them a long time ago...
Juan Yun: But he made these special for today—just for Arbiter Maeok.
Tindoiimu: Wow... so rare.
Juan Yun: Yep, and to be able to enjoy these here with the princess... guess it was worth stealing them from the stage.
Tindoiimu: ...As always, the lord loves to joke around...
Juan Yun: You think that was a joke~?
Juan Yun: By the way, Is your injury getting any better?
Tindoiimu: It's still painful, but... at least I'm able to walk a bit.
Juan Yun: I'm sorry, I... didn't mean to let you get hurt.
Tindoiimu: ...It was the assassin. It wasn't your fault.
Juan Yun: Here, this is medicine I had a foreign friend of mine bring me. It's said to be miraculous. Please take it.
Tingko: Princess!
Tindoiimu: Tingko!
Tingko: I'm sorry. They stopped me and accused us of trying to flee...
Qilin Guard: Think you can all run away!? After this, none of you will be allowed outside again!
Jihasaha: Let go—
Juan Yun: ...Harassing this young lady right before my eyes. Do you want me to lose face right in front of the princess?
Qilin Guard: L-Lord! We didn't see you there—
Juan Yun: So if I weren't here, then you'd continue to mistreat this young woman?
Juan Yun: This sullies the reputation of our tribe immensely, and you have still not released Miss Tingko!
Qilin Guard: Y-Yes, sir!
Tindoiimu: They didn't hurt you, did they?
Tingko: I'm fine... I'm very grateful for Lord Juan Yun, but I still don't understand why he keeps getting so worked up...
Tindoiimu: Yeah, I know...
Juan Yun: Listen here! Women should be treated with the utmost—
Juan Yun: Ah, the medicine!
Qilin Guard: Lord, be careful!
Qilin Guard: Waaarrrghhh!!!
Jihasaha: They're coming!
Tingko: H-Have these people been bewitched!? Why did they suddenly—
Jihasaha: Don't worry about that now! Let's get back to the main street and find some people to help!
Alliance Soldier: Move according to our orders! Do not run astray and do not push or shove!
Alliance Soldier: Quit looking around. Get out of here fast and get somewhere safe!
Tindoiimu: What's happening!?
Tingko: Wah!
Frightened Citizen: R-Run!!!!
Flurried Citizen: They came charging in! If we don't run, they'll catch up with us!
Lost Child: Grandpa... mommy... *sob*...
Terrified Citizen: Help!! Somebody's been killed!!
Juan Yun: I am Juan Yun, Lord of the Qilin Tribe. Could you please tell us what is going on here?
Alliance Soldier: Lord of the Qilin Tribe? What are you doing here!? Something big happened at the Peace Ceremony, you didn't hear!?
Juan Yun: What!?
Alliance Soldier: No time to explain! Hurry up and follow the crowd!
???: H-Help!
Tingko: Those clothes! Like from the ceremony... It's Miss Soohyeon of the Kyo Tribe!
Juan Yun: What? Is it really Soohyeon!?
Flurried Citizen: Eeee! Those people have all been bewitched! Run!!
Jihasaha: They're headed this way. Can we save her?
Soohyeon: Juan Yun! Tindoiimu! Help...!
Tindoiimu: .........
Tindoiimu: We must. She's a good person.
